{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17489163","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17489163"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T04:07:19+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T04:07:19+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"607"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"607","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/607"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.12,0.65,0.02,0.15,0.06]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"607"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"102657"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"607","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/607"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"607"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"85137"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"11"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"30"},{"type":"tags","id":"31"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"316"},{"type":"tags","id":"1087"},{"type":"tags","id":"8118"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"2525"},{"type":"contributions","id":"2758"},{"type":"contributions","id":"31890"},{"type":"contributions","id":"35992"},{"type":"contributions","id":"41900"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"102657","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/102657"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EAn otherwise well 56-year-old woman presents to her general practitioner with a two month history of a cough, which has not resolved. She is a lifelong non-smoker. The physical examination is unremarkable. A chest X-ray is performed (Image).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Squamous cell lung carcinoma","Adenocarcinoma of the lung","Neuroendocrine lung carcinoma","Small cell lung carcinoma","Large cell lung carcinoma"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe history of this patient is concerning and the chest X-ray shows a mass in the left upper lobe in the periphery of the lung. Hence, a lung cancer would be a top differential cause of the mass. Epidemiological data can help to radiologically predict which carcinoma it may be, but this cannot be confirmed until after a biopsy has been done to gain a histological diagnosis. This will also guide the most appropriate management option.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThere are two main types of lung cancer, these being \u003Cstrong\u003Esmall cell lung cancer\u003C/strong\u003E and non-small cell lung cancer. The majority (85-90%) are non-small cell lung cancers. There are three subtypes of non-small cell lung cancer, these being;\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003Esquamous cell carcinoma\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003Eadenocarcinoma\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003Elarge cell carcinoma\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAdenocarcinoma has the strongest association with peripheral masses, whereas squamous cell and small cell carcinoma tend to produce a central mass. Large cell typically are peripheral, but they are much less common than adenocarcinoma. They are usually seen as large peripheral masses on the chest X-ray. Adenocarcinoma is also the most common cause of lung cancer in non-smokers, and is more common in women than men, unlike the other lung cancers, which are generally more common in men.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENeuroendocrine lung cancers\u003C/strong\u003E are relatively rare, they can also cause cushing syndrome or carcinoid syndrome if the cells within the tumour become active and secreting hormones.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHence based on the history, the X-ray findings and epidemiological data the most likely cause of this woman\u0027s symptoms is an adenocarcinoma of the lung.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Adenocarcinoma of the lung most commonly presents with peripheral masses","Small cell and squamous cell carcinoma of the lung most commonly present with central masses","Adenocarcinoma of the lung is the most common lung cancer in non-smokers"],"references":["Cancer Australia. Types of lung cancer. 2020. Australian Government. Access at: https://www.canceraustralia.gov.au/affected-cancer/cancer-types/lung-cancer/types-lung-cancer.","Dubin S, Griffin D. Lung Cancer in Non-Smokers. Mo Med. 2020;117(4):375-379.","Dela Cruz CS, Tanoue LT, Matthay RA. Lung cancer: epidemiology, etiology, and prevention. Clin Chest Med. 2011;32(4):605-644. doi:10.1016/j.ccm.2011.09.001"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"85137"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"607"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"18440"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"18440","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/18440"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/a11fb42a-8017-4049-9e3e-418f1f78b841.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/a11fb42a-8017-4049-9e3e-418f1f78b841.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":363,"height":440}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"85137","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/85137"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-05-14T08:43:56+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-05-14T08:45:08+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"607"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"102657"}}},"met